  <name>Bulk Renamer</name>
  <summary>Powerful batch file renaming</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Bulk Renamer is a powerful, GNOME-native bulk file renaming application
      written in Rust. It provides an intuitive interface for renaming multiple
      files using various rules.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Find and replace text in filenames</li>
      <li>Change case (lowercase, UPPERCASE, Title Case, etc.)</li>
      <li>Insert text at various positions</li>
      <li>Remove text patterns</li>
      <li>Add sequential numbering</li>
      <li>Insert date/time from file metadata</li>
      <li>Preview changes before applying</li>
      <li>Safe validation, undo support, and rename logs</li>
      <li>Save and load presets</li>
      <li>Import direct rename mappings from CSV</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Some advanced rule editors are still being completed; the core engine
      supports more rule types than the current interface exposes.
    </p>
  </description>
